author: Carmen Cox
title: Joey Logano Wins First Race of Chase's ‘Contender Round’
text:
Share Article 
Jared C. Tilton/Getty Images (CONCORD, N.C.) — Joey Logano on Sunday won the first race of the "Contender Round," the second phase of the Sprint Cup Series' Chase.Logano edged defending champ Kevin Harvick by .704 seconds for the win in the Bank of America 500. The victory earns him a spot in the next round of the Chase.It was Logano's fourth win of the season.The Bank of America 500 was initially scheduled for Saturday night, but was postponed due to rain.Here are the top 10 drivers in the Bank of America 500, held at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, North Carolina:1. Joey Logano
